<br />
The PS3 is slowly picking up steam. It had a slow start for a couple of reasons:<br />
1) It was last to the market, and a year trailing its main competition, the Xbox360.<br />
2) It was more expensive than the other consoles, but is in a good position going forward with the BluRay drive and ever lowering costs.<br />
3) It had a far smaller library than the 360, and virtually no playable exclusives. This is slowly changing as well, as studios catch up and begin releasing PS3 games simultaneously with the 360 version (rather than the delay you saw with Orange Box).<br />
<br />
The PS3 will slowly gain steam and be successful. The overall capabilities of the machine are outstanding, it just needed the games on the shelf to start selling the system. I&#39;m not saying it&#39;ll catch the 360 or Wii, but it&#39;ll definitely do pretty well in its own right.  <br><BR><font size=1>09:20 12-14-2007</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' bgcolor=#CCCCCC>&nbsp;</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#CCCCCC><font class="bfont"><B>Ken B</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#CCCCCC' ><font class="bfont">Ha!  I just realized I&#39;d looked at those numbers wrong...the PS2 *still* outsold the PS3!  Bwahahahahahahahahahaha! <br><BR><font size=1>09:14 12-14-2007</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' bgcolor=#FFFFFF>&nbsp;</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>Ken B</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#FFFFFF' ><font class="bfont">New numbers for November (credit 411mania for culling the info)<br />
